field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Jazz4 is 10nm Ir on 5 nm Ti on GC, Reshma1B was 25nm RuO2 sputtered at RT on 5nm Ti on GC
field_data.Removed from vacuum: Jazz4 in air since last time, Reshma1B removed from omicron a couple days ago

notes: less active than RuO2, but we knew this. Activity falls during potential hold, but we knew this. Held for a bit longer (5 min and 10 min) for more accurate O2 calibration) Then calibrated RHE. It's not moved more than a couple mV. Looks maybe like 0.718, but gonna keep using 0.720. ----- Reshma1B ------- Reason for doing this is that Reshma1F, which had a milder reduction and oxidation treatment than Reshma1B, only had a little bit of 18O in I.S.S, so had to do it again. Reshma1B happens to be the sample that we did get a 2:1 18O:16O ratio in with its previous treatment, but then Jakob sputtered away the outer monolayer, so its reset. 01... all looks good, and indeed, Reshma1B looks like it did before. Comparing to 18H31, it's got the same capacitance, just shifted 10 mV (due to RHE potential) and steeper because it didn't have the resistor then. Giving it 20 cycles from -0.050 V vs RHE to 1.50 V vs RHE with 1 minute holds at each potential limit, scan rate 20 mV/s. In the mean while, using the hydrogen line and roughing pump to empty the reduction valve of the methane bottle so I can move the bottle outside. O2 and H2 signals get gradually noisier each cycle of 12, but CV stable. Capacitance seems unchanged at 5 mV/s after the bigh cycles. Don't really recover the smooth MS signals when checking activity again at the end, and finish a bit clumsily. Done with 18O electrolyte!!!
